reviews.text:
Had such an incredible experience at this North Indian gem of a restaurant!

Went here for their weekend buffet and was blown away by Everything - from the impeccable service, to the rich & delicious North Indian cuisine, to the amazing Indian decor and even the music was incredible & really set the vibe for the whole restaurant! It was Instrumental Indian Flute Songs that has been added to my Spotify :)

The weekend buffet runs on Saturdays and Sundays from 11:30 AM - 2:30 PM and costs only $19. Its an absolute STEAL of a deal - I would happily pay $25 or $30 for the buffet - but don't tell the owners that :D

I got in there right at opening, so was able to get some nice pics of all the buffet dishes! Here was what was on the menu when I went:
***Lasooni Palak, Mutter Mushroom, Dal Makhani, Paneer Lababdar, Aloo Tamatar, Murgh Makhni, Tandoori Murg, & Lamb Curry*** (Definitely recommend you Google each dish to get a Really good idea of all the ingredients and what goes into them)

The first 5 dishes listed are vegetarian and the last 3 are non-veg, so there is something for everyone. I tried everything and all of the dishes were deliciousssss and 5 stars all around!

If you've been craving some North Indian cuisine where you will be treated like Royalty & enjoy a meal fit for a king or queen, Jaipur's weekend lunch buffet is the place to go!

The settings of the restaurant were very beautiful and luxurious. Also, the food was ad good as everything else. I ordered online and picked from the store. The website is very easy to use. And the service is great.

I love this place! It has really nice decorations and atmosphere, most importantly really good food and service.  I like how all the waiters help one another it’s not just one person serving our table all of them asks us if we need water refill or anything else so it’s super easy to order more nann or needing anything else.   We’ve only ever gotten nann and the chicken tikka masala and it’s so good!  The portion size of the chicken masala is so fair and generous and I love how there is a lot of sauce (because I like putting it on rice and dipping the nann in it a lot of places don’t have enough sauce) and the chicken pieces are cut well, not in huge chunks like at many Indian restaurants so the chicken chunks are a lot more flavorful and not like just 4 pieces each piece the size of a small child’s fist that it’s hard to share 😂.  The chicken tikka masala is very flavorful、not watery or run down sauce like at some places (thinking about curry mantra), or too tomatoey sauce tasting (other places we’ve been to) and comes with a generous portion of rice.  Compared to lots of other Indian restaurants in the area, this is one of our top picks that we always end up picking over the others!  Highly recommend for good food, well cooked, good service and very generous portions.
Nice decor and colorful dining place. Lamb chops and chicken tandoori were tasty but over grilled and slightly burnt.

Great food, Great service. Call in and make reservations, we had just walked in. They did make arrangements for us to dine in.
Shall visit again with reservations. We enjoyed our dinner. Missed taking pictures of food, as we were busy enjoying the food 😃

name: Mary's Restaurant Pollo A La Brasa

reviews.text: I was at Haley's laundromat and I saw this place called Mary's restaurant right next to the laundromat so I gave it a try. I ordered the steak and cheese with fries and I added a side of the chicken tamale. I also added a couple pepsis. The food was excellent. The chicken tamale was made with a chicken wing and he left the bone in to add more flavor. The tamale was very moist and very delicious just a tad of spice but very tasty. The Steak and Cheese Sandwich was really good too. The sandwich had a  toasted sub roll with steak cheese lettuce tomato and light mayonnaise perfectly made and that was a companied by crispy fries. Overall the meal was excellent. As I was waiting for my laundry to complete next door I was able to have a good meal at Mary's restaurant located at  Fairfax circle next to Citco.

Great food! I ordered the pupusas. They were amazing and the price is really good.
The fried plantains were a little soggy but still good.
Food here is really great and super yummy but the service is absolutely trash. Everytime we go to this restaurant they are so rude and even mess up our orders sometimes.
Let me say first, I love the hard working folks at this place. Organic and authentic food. Friendly staff. I highly recommend if you want quite place and authentic Latin American food.

I was here last time 3 years ago when I lived in this area. I always enjoy the food here and I recommend to everyone to try it. NOT TODAY. PLEASE AVOID this place. It turn in dirty and unhygienic place. I'm so sad to lose the best sopa de res and charcoal Peruvian chicken. Why 2 stars? Because of the costumes service from one person (male/cashier)

Good service. I think pancakes are great. Not that great as the hype created. Overall good experience. You can other stuff tho. Fries, chicken and burgers

My second visit after two months. I tried chocolate pan cakes. They were 5 star delicious stacked cakes. Must try

This is one of the best ihops I have been to so far. Large with plenty of seating, booths, parking and outdoor dining. It’s in a nice spot with its own parking lot and trees around it. The staff are nice.

It was good. Served fast. Tasty. Cheap. Typical iHop, nothing unusual. But I poured so much maple sirup on those pancakes that I got such a sugar high ))))) I was out for like 30 min. And of course I had a a burger with fries which added 15 min to my coma ))))

We had a nice breakfast. My company was afraid of the quality overall. We had a good experience. There was good service. Food was good and filling. My husband particularly like the crepes. He was impressed about the flavor and  variety (lingenberry). We are coming back. I'm sorry we didn't try it sooner. Disadvantages: it felt slightly crowded at 8:30 am. The place seems slightly old.

Great breakfast foods for everytime of day. Pancakes are some of the best I have ever had. Service was amazing. Was sitting outside with rain falling and still server came out to check up on us to make sure we had everything we needed.

I usually have no problems with this chic fila but this time....make sure you don't order breakfast if it's close to lunchtime. I ordered a breakfast bowl and it's looks like they picked the eggs out the trash because that's all they could find. I have a little PIECE of egg. It would've been better if they just canceled my breakfast instead of not making it correctly!

Great food, fairly inexpensive and people are always nice. Facilities are clean, it wasn't packed, so great experience overall. It's not as large as some of the locations outside of heavily populated areas, but they still have a drive thru and all that. There's even a cow with lights on it outside.

This Chick-fil-A has a nicer appearance outside than others I've seen, and the inside was nicely decorated for Christmas, which was a pleasant touch. However, it is smaller than others I've been to, and the drive through line can block parking spaces. The service was very fast and quite friendly and the food tasted good, but not very hot. The table we sat at inside was dirty but brought to the attention of an employee,  quickly remedied. Overall I had a good experience at this Chick-fil-A and I'm glad I visited.
Great chicken 🐔  fast food. Friendly staff.

There was a crowd on Saturday afternoon, but service was good.  We only got vanilla cones--really ice milk but good flavor (though the cones were stale/slightly tough)--and a brownie.  The brownie was fabulous and worth returning for.

This was our go-to Domino's because it is one of two closest to us.  For a long time it was consistently satisfactory, and we gave it a solid four stars.  It's recently taken a dive downhill.  First, we submitted an order for pickup.  Turned out the order either never was produced or had been given to someone else.  We had to wait nearly 20 minutes for the order to be re-produced.  Zero apologies.  Second, we ordered two three-topping pizzas for 9.49 each.  One was two toppings and was priced at $9.49.  The other had three toppings but was priced at $10.99.  Why?  Because we had asked for a double portion of one topping.  The location refused even the minimal compensation of giving us a bottle of soda in lieu of a refund of $1.50.  At least we got an insincere "we're sorry" this time.  Go here at risk of major disappointment.
AVOID

If I could give 0 stars I would. We placed our order and it was already going to take an hour. So an hour and a half goes by and we still don't have our food. Our driver left the store 45 minutes before our food got here.

We called and complained. The manager at least offered us a refund without much hassle. That's not the point though. I would rather have spent the money, gotten my order in a reasonable amount of time, and had a decent meal.

Instead, our food got here lukewarm and the driver didn't even bring our entire order. Look how sad this pepperoni pizza looks.

Avoid. Don't waste your time.

I haven't had dominos in awhile and today we ordered a pan pizza and the dough was raw. Super disappointing when you're working all day and super hungry. I'm not sure why a place that specializes in pizza can not bake a pizza as it should be baked. Hard to tell in the pic but I assure you it is super soft AFTER baking it myself for an extra amount of time!

Worst domino's. Choose another one or another pizza place in general. Pizza is always missing hot sauce (even though its under the ingredient list and not super hard to miss) and arrives cold continuously. I told the delivery guy that my order was wrong (no hot sauce on top) be he just told me to "call the store". Bought a marble brownie this time and it is burnt (didn't check it before he left because how can you mess that up). How do you let these items leave the store? Not ordering from here again. Management is lacking.
Workers and food sucked. The pizza tasted sad and the banana peppers were white which I've never seen before. They were also tasteless

name: Starbucks
vicinity: 3011 Nutley Street Pan Am Shopping Center, Fairfax

reviews.text: The drink I ordered looked like the milk was spoiled. I asked if I can change it and the barista was very rude starting to redo the same one without asking if I wanted the same one. Obviously I didn’t want the same one as the products were not ok and of course the new drink came out the same as the first. Couldn’t drink it!
The employees at this location are amazing. Most friendly team I have experienced. So happy this is close to home.
A smaller location but they have some seating. It’s very clean with nice public restrooms. The staff is kind. When they were out of something, they had good suggestions for a replacement drink.
Great place to study, good staff, quick service, great cold drinks!

I ordered cold brewed coffee with light ice. Not only she filled the cup with ice, she but added tap water to the cup before pouring the cold coffee. This is ridiculously the most expensive "flavored ice" you could buy.
PS: the photo shows the ice after about 45 min from my order. Imagine how much ice was in there when I got it.

Wow, where to even begin? Entrance is well taken care of with outdoor seating available in the shade. Quite a large outdoor space, they did put the space to great use! Great menu items, I was left with many thins to chose from!! Our host was nice, he was very friendly. The downfall was the arrival for the food to come to our table. It took approximately 40 minutes to get our food, the bacon and cheese burger with seasoned fries. It just the two of us, and it wasn’t that busy. I loved the fact that each table did have their individual TV the watch the show one wished for. The burger was well cooked, juicy and tender. Nicely seasoned bacon, and fries. Mango Ice Tea was flavourful. I will be back again but I hope that our wait time isn’t long.

Our first restaurant dinner in our new city! And very close to our new home! JC took good care of us as we sat outside in the beautiful fall weather. We both ordered off the Octoberfest menu. When JC brought me a refill - Coca Cola products -  (for which I didn't have to ask for), I mentioned to him that I had ordered my Prussian Pretzel Roll without onions. Sure enough, there were onions in it! Not wanting to be a glitch customer, I ate it anyway. JC talked to the kitchen and another roll was prepared, without onions.The fries were hot and crispy when. delivered. The chicken schnnitzel was enjoyed as well. The service we received and the food will make us a repeat customer. Be prepared for large portions!

UPDATE: It was so good the first time we had to go back for fish and chips two days later! We sat outside once again and were treated to a gorgeous sunset. Food was good and served hot. Water w/lemon slice was delivered as our server approached to take our order. Ketchup and malt vinegar were also delivered promptly. The downside? I had asked for extra lemon for my fish and did nnot receive it. Our server (not JC) never checked back to see how our meal was. I know it was busy and he was taking care of other patrons, but it would have taken 1 minute to stop by. While I wish it was haddock, our cod was very good and crisp. We love this place in our new neighborhood and will be back again and again!

UPDATE December 11, 2021
Another meal at our favorite local restaurant. First time eating inside. Much bigger than expected. TV’s on every wall. Excellent fish and chips. Served hot and crispy  good service as we’ve come to expect. Seasonal specials. Will be back again.

UPDATE: January 7, 2022
Another fish fry Friday at our favorite local restauant. AND we reconnected with our first server - JC. He remembered us and of course we received his excellent service ad enjoyed our conversations. I even had dessert - Cherry Cobbler - which I never order dessert!  We have relatives visiting in February and hope to bring them to Glory Days for lunch. Will ask for JC's section and hope he'll be on duty that day. As always, the food was hot and good. Extra tartar sauce and plenty of extra lemons delivered. Soda refill without asking. Stella on draft. Clean restrooms. Great place to eat when you want someone else todo the cooking!

Service is always quick and friendly.  Food hot, and tasty.  Atmosphere is happy with beautiful smiling faces, and the environment is clean. Love this place.  The impossible steak and cheese are not on the menu. But if you ask, they will always make it. Absolutely delicious.

I order from here a lot when I’m dog sitting as it’s right around the corner. Always great food! I recently ordered a steak, mashed potatoes and chicken tenders. All were really good. Also came with a “side” Caesar salad. It was big enough that I ate it for lunch the next day. Great place!

This is one of my favorites for easy, casual food but food today wasn't up to their usual standard.  For some reason, the fried chicken on my salad smelled like cookies (and the coating tasted the same).  And my friend's nachos didn't have a lot of flavor, even with chili on them.  But their ranch dressing is the best in the area! And they have dog friendly outdoor seating.

Family-owned, strip-mall gem of a restaurant. Feels like a diner, menu plates from classic Greek dishes, good old American cheeseburgers, and delicious homemade soups. The vintage style interior deco may take you back to the 70’s era but once you take a seat, leave your iPhone off – leisurely take it all in.

This was the best place for 43 years or so. The menu keeps changing, the options are fewer, the prices go up. George is still there; yay!!!
The dessert case is gone and has been replaced with a counter and stool chairs. (They still offer desserts, but not as many).
The world has changed and they are adapting to the changes too. It’s still a place to go but it’s not the same. The salad bar was among the best, it’s long gone.
Go and see for yourself!
My favorite eggplant is $19 now and came with soup, not salad. Maybe if I had asked…?

This is a great local Greek restaurant that is one of the last long time institutions at Pan Am Shopping Center.  Filled with regular customers who greet each other like foamily.  They recently trimmed down their menu to a mere three pages, but kept all of their favorite breakfast and Greek dishes.  Food is as good as always, coffee is always freshly made.  Skip the overly pricing brunch spots and give these folks a try.

It had been a while since I had been so I took some coworkers for their first time.  Lunch was very good. I suggested the gyro sandwiches and everyone had them. No complaints.  Consistently good food for decades now.

This morning, I had breakfast at Pan Am based on a friend's recommendation.  Like the other reviews mentioned, this is a family owned business with service and food at excellent quality and reasonable prices.  No waiting in long lines similar to other breakfast spots.  Try the French Toast platter - real brioche bread!

Stop by to grab a coffee and a wrap use my rewards, buy a coffee get a free wrap. They were not able to ring my order up to utilize the reward so the manager offered me donut instead. The place is clean my order was good I passed this place every day coming from work and never stopped. I will be back
made a mobile order earlier today & it was missing an item. there was no one at the counter when i went to ask for help. other than that, it's an alright dunkins

Arrived approx 7:30 pm. Got 2 sour cream (very good); 1 chocolate cake (lacked good flavor - don't know, if blindfolded, I could identify); 1 regular glazed (disappointingly stale - since they no longer fry on-site, you must discriminate late in day.)
Can only depend on cake style to maintain moisture level.
My husband and I used to depend on Dunkin' for delicious end-of-date donuts & coffees after movies and dancing our feet off. Makes me sad today's young couples can't enjoy likewise.

Avoid on National Donut day...super crowded and looked like they were understaffed and unprepared. Asked for cream and sugar in the Dunkin’ midnight coffee and also a chocolate glazed donut but received a chocolate donut (not the same as chocolate glazed) and also a black coffee with NO cream and sugar. Extremely disappointed given the wait was 30 min+ to get your order.

Ordered sour cream donut and it was taken from that tray but it had some blueberries in it. Also bought a plain classic donut but it had a weird spice in it that sort of reminds me of an Indian spice but I could be mistaken. Just not what I expected from a plain Dunkin’ Donut

Skyrocketed Prices!!!!!!! I really don't follow the design of their menu.

Staff are nice and accommodating. Really nice ambiance. Cool lighting and ample public parking spaces.

A proper bar setup. And really cool seating setup ideal for big social dining.

I just can’t find a reason to justify their prices. I was going through previous reviews and I saw and response from mgmt that it is the big portions are the reason for inflated rates, But the portions aren’t big as they claim.

This is a traditional Japanese style shabu-shabu hot pot place with high quality meat hidden inside of a local strip mall in fairfax. please don't compare this to Korean or Chinese All you can eat hot pot as it's a different category.

From the ponzu and sesame dipping sauce it immediately reminded me of Shabu-Shaba restaurants from Japan town in San Francisco. (Not sure if that's where the inspiration came from for their name of the restaurant itself.)

As soon as I sat down to take a glance at the sake menu, I knew this place was serious about  the attention to detail with picking the sake and the quality of food. My personal favorite being the 'demom slayer's Wakatake Onikoroshi a Junmai Daiginjo & Dassai 23 another Junmai Daiginjo which pairs perfectly with shabu shabu in my opinion. The sake was also served perfectly chilled through a Hario ice dispenser ( glass funnel-like concoction that has ice in a separate glass so you don't dilute the sake and it's self-served). Before we could finish the first bottle Duke provided a bottle of Amabuki, a rose colored sake that was made with black rice.

So for the food, first of all, this is not an all you can eat hot pot place but focus on quality meat and seafood .For beef ribeye you have an option between choice prime, Kobe and over the top. A5 wagyu . I went for the middle of the road prime ribeye and honestly the King Kong portion of prime beef is perfect if not a little large for a single person. When we visited with the large party of 10 plus on a week day, the entire staff were very accommodating and the service was also attentive.

The edamame and sweet potato fries were favorites for my young kids while the prime beef shabu shabu was with standard Kombu broth was just perfect. A few of our friends tried the spicy miso which was also great. As far as the meat goes, I thought it was perfectly sliced and had great marbling.  Everyone, including the staff and especially Duke the owner came out to make sure everything was perfect throughout the meal.

thank you for an excellent meal we'll be back

Really enjoyed the spicy miso soup broth. Delicious variety of veggies and meat. Also try the Cashu buns super yummy!
Thank you to the helpful wait staff!

Very clean restaurant. The server was very friendly and helpful with the explanation of how to eat the hotpot. We went here for the hidden Vietnamese item "bun dau mam tom" and were very pleased with it. Overall, it was a very satisfactory experience.

Come here. Eat. Enjoy. My first time here and it was awesome! I was a little confused about the process, but the flavor made up for my ignorance. Great atmosphere. Amazing service. Spectacular food! Priced is proper for everything. I WILL BE BACK!! 👍🏾
I love their food, but the prices have gotten astronomical and even though their location is 10 minutes or less from my house, Uber Eats orders always take at least an hour.
The food ummmm and the queso llanero omg .you have to go to this place, is in the back entrance the girls are super nice.  All the sweets  we grew up having , are there.  Have fun and Blesses
My favorite place to recharge Venezuelan’s flavors!

I just discovered this little jewel in Fairfax after 2 years in VA. Great empanadas, cachapas, tequeños and arepas with authentic Venezuelan flavor. I wish they had more locations like this around the DMV 😪
The arepas were amazing. Adding plantain in there for a sweet and salty flavor was perfect.

This is one of those places that from the outside you wouldn't give it a second thought.  But trust me, go in!  The service is friendly and the Pho is amazing.  It may not be the flashiest place you have ever been, but really, who cares. The food is great! Don't pass this place by, go in and enjoy!

I pay 25$ for two children noodle soup the noodle and little,little bit chicken, little bit souce I will never ever go there again. I will go to the one in Fairfax are always great and better for your money.I will love to leave no star at all if I could. Look there really dirty for what I pay for.

Food was good. Service attentive without being over bearing. But service also a bit whacky. They brought us the summer rolls and spring rolls pictured despite them not being our order. When we told them the first guy just kept going - definitely some confusion ensued. The stuff we did order was good though. I'd go back.

I have never dined in but always ordered to go. I work in the area and saw how close they were and with the previous reviews I decided to try them out. IM SO GLAD I DID! The broth is very good along with the meat and noodles. I also tried the Vermicelli Bowl with Pork and Egg rolls and definitely was great. The people who took my order were very nice and checked me out in a timely manner. My food was always ready to go as soon as I arrived. Can't wait to try to dine in one of these days :)

This is my favorite pho place and I’ve been to many - including pho 75 which is supposed to be really authentic and the best. This place is better in my opinion, and they’re so sweet and kind.

I love their spring rolls, their “just steak” pho option and their lime sodas. Good comes out hot and fast.
Clean, delicious options and so affordable! I use this bar for my lunches and dinners. Fantastic addition to the neighborhood.

Brought the kids, six and four and they LOVED it. Place is delicious, clean, and service was spectacular. It was slow, so they showed the kids the ovens and gave them balloons. Fun place with great food.
Good foods, number of choices and very delicious. Served directly from charcoal grills and you can taste the difference. Highly recommend, Enjoy.

I was pretty overwhelmed by the choices as they all sounded really good. I end up asking the owner who was there to help me with my choice and he did not disappoint! Extremely friendly, helpful and respectful guy. Me and my partner end up getting the loco moco half white. Not only was the chicken cooked perfectly (the chicken breast was juicy and not dry at all) the sauce pairing was on point as well. Would definitely come back and recommend to friends and family.

Stop in for a quick bite before a holiday party. The food was delicious! We were planning to have some leftovers for later after the party but ended up eating all of it. The yucca was fantastic, super crispy and fresh. We added a pupusa to try and they made it fresh on the spot! We're definitely going back and definitely grabbing a family meal for dinner soon! More people need to know about this place!!!!

Definitely the most delicious charcoal chicken I ate in DMV! I liked the variety of dishes and menu, I ordered half chicken with yucca, it was yummy!!! I liked how the chicken was cooked and the skin was crispy! I'll go here more often after gym since it is a healthy food. It is halal and staff are friendly as well. I wish it was closer to my home.
Great for sushi plate
Good 🍣 especially for inside a Safeway store.
Not 24 hour

I have been going here since I have moved to Vienna because I love how they make their food. Some the renovation they were closed for a very long time but they finally opened back up! Yes! I mean you got to try their pad thai, calamari, and spicy eggplant tofu. They don't try to cheat their portions and generous with ingredients. So, if you are craving some take outs or eat ins for Thai, then try them out. Easy parking too!

I would totally recommend this place!
I ordered Bangkok st spicy noodle and they were delicious. The quantity is great and spiciness is on point. (The picture shows the leftovers)
I also ordered calamari but they were just basic, I wish the batter would have had less egg so it would have been a little less smelly.

Lad na means Gravy over noodle. This is one of my favorite noodle dishes as I grew up in Chinatown, Thailand.  This is very good one.  It is very hard to find a cook who can make good tasty authentic gravy over noodle to get it taste right.  You should try it once.
One of the best places to eat Tom Yum shrimp soup. Very authentic and excellent flavor. Their fried rice is also very well made. Definitely coming back again.

The server was nice, food was good. I liked the mango sticky rice desert.
Unfortunately there is no WiFi but I am okay with that. Good experience all around 5stars.

Very good lunch options. The service was great, the place very clean, and ultimately you can see the pride in it.

I enjoyed the fried chicken, but the spicy/sweet was a tad sweet for my liking.

We got the Garlic Soy and Snowed Garlic Spicy chicken along with sides of fries. Both super tasty, flavorful and fresh with lots of crunchy texture  from the breading. Highly recommend this pairing of the two types of chicken too as it was a nice contrast. Fries were okay, but then again that's not the star of the show here.
The chicken is hot and fresh, and the sauces are nice. They really need to upgrade from their flimsy plastic cutlery. Offering chopsticks to white people would also be helpful.

DO NOT GO THERE, PLEASE READ BELOW!!!

Ordered food and employee said I can’t eat inside , otherwise it will charge 18% additional, but sign says 18% additional on 6 people or more (picture added) not coming back and not recommended, this is not how you do business, not allowing customers eating inside!!! Literally inside was sitting 2 people, lots of empty tables,  I don’t understand Why?
Young man (he’s big liar as well)  who was working there today, unprofessional and need to be learn how to provide service! I came there to eat and got kicked outside for no reason (outside was over 100 degrees hot and humid)
Paid for chicken wings almost $16 (side order additional) got no sauce,  no napkins and chicken was tasteless.

Takes chicken wings to a new level.  They don't have the usual wings place array of sauces, but the chicken is great. You will be full after 5 wings but then keep eating because it is so good.  Outdoor seating under cover.
Decided to try a new place and boy am I happy I did!! Amazing Ramen… all the food was amazing! Service was impeccable and atmosphere chill!

The review was so good that I went with high expectations. The interior of the store was so good. But the taste was not as good as expected. The ramen taste was just so so. The meat smelled a little. Chicken Kara Age tasted different from Japanese restaurants. It wasn't good. I think this is just a normal ramen restaurant.

Visited the first time on a whim and was surprised at the atmosphere given the entrance, but the interior is a true gem. Chill vibes, amazing service, and insanely delicious food. Try everything. You won't be disappointed.

Pretty nice place, just opened too. Price is a bit much, tho you do get a lot in return, other than that it's good.

Both of their dessert offerings are great, amazing green tea flavors.
Great place for good ramen! New and clean inside, very pleasant atmosphere, polite and friendly staff. Ramen was very good, I’ll definitely come back!

The first couple times I came here, I had a really good time. The music was good, the vibe was chill, DJ Ankor was mixing all the genres of music. But when I recently went there, it was not the same. First, I had to wait 45 mins just for my hookah. The music was way too loud, it was a different DJ. I don’t know if that DJ had any experience because he did not know how to mix the music so it was hard to vibe and have fun. Imo they need to bring the old DJs back.

This lounge is amazing!!!
I've been looking for a hookah lounge and this place is has what I'm looking for!
Great hookah, delicious drinks and great djs!
Ali was amazing he took care of my friends and I!
Definitely won't be my last time.

I can only comment on the customer service of this place. The people are super friendly and great. I had a situation where I wanted to watch Sunday night football and the worker  looked for a while trying to find it. He did not have to but that was a nice gesture.

I have been to this place twice. I thought the second time they would atleast improvise in their services but sadly it was the same. The D.J is excellent, no doubt!
But I don't know how but they charged $300 for just 3 people. We didn't even eat anything there. When I asked for bill, they kept me waiting and I had to leave then. I would request the owner that please provide the bill atleast and mention the prices of each and everything. People come to your place to have some good time, expecting a decent service, not to get charged unecessarily.

I would definitely agree with what Sam N said. While the first time visiting was quite fun, the following two other visits were not quite so much. After seating ourselves we  waited nearly 45 minutes and never got attended or acknowledged. The two table next to us also had the same issue and had to come up to a bartender to get help. Hookah was alright after fixing it ourselves and the dj was actually really nice and played good music. When it came to paying their system automatically tipped themselves 20% gratuity without telling you and asks for another tip on top of that as if you didn't tip already. Not only that they sneakily charge you extra stuff so I'd be careful of that. They were charging me 80 dollars for 3 drinks and a hookah. Wouldn't come back because it was the second time theyve done something like this to me or a friend. Definitely not worth the price.

MOST DEFINITELY A TOP CONTENDER 🔥 🐔 🔥
I would always get my chicken from little Peru but I love to give others a chance for the crown and Max's chicken did not come to play!!
I arrived half hour before closing but the lady treated me so kindly still and was very friendly. I got the family special of a whole chicken, 3 sides and a soda for 28.99!! Food came out quickly after ordering and the cashier even went out of their way to give me plates and utensils to go.
